body:
Guess the Avicadian!

This might not prove a hugely popular game, but we'll see how it goes.

With this, you have to write 3 clues below in the comments about someone you know on Avicus. It can't be a personal thing about them (it's unlikely you know anything personal about them anyway) or something embarrassing - it has to be purely about Avicus.

So, I'll start. Write in the comments below who you think it is, and the first person to get it right will be confirmed by me. I might not be there to answer all the time, so please fill in where necessary and someone else can do it.

Here we go then....

        Clue 1: He has recently been promoted to Jr Moderator
        Clue 2: MB.
        Clue 3: Best friend of mine <3

Who is it?

Happy gaming,

                                                  _Za

P.S can we get this game 25k views? <3 (20.3k on old website, so can we get it?)

replies.body:
Yes, and for multiple reasons. It has almost ten thousand more views, nearly two and a half times as many posts, and an approachable incisiveness that makes it easy for anyone to participate in, the latter of which is probably the reason for the former two. Whereas that thread follows the simple format of rate after rate, this one often falls into disarray with people frequently guessing incorrectly and then posting clues that sometimes never get responded to. It's also substantially easier to estimate a player's skill level (even if by just looking at their statistics) than to try figuring out the username of somebody you've never encountered or heard of.

The other thread is basically friendlier and more succinct in general such that anyone on the forums can play. In a place where the people are encouraged to coalesce as one community, it would make sense to prioritize that.
